text.paragraph:
In patients with impaired liver function, parenteral nutrition solutions containing PROSOL should be administered starting at the low end of the dosing range [see Dosage and Administration (2.5)]. Frequent clinical evaluation and laboratory tests to monitor liver function such as bilirubin and liver function parameters should be conducted [see 

                              Warnings and Precautions (5.7)

                           ].

For storage of admixed solutions [see 

